name: 2-Methoxyethanol
Reason: 2-Methoxyethanol is a derivative of ethanol, which has a melting point of -114.1°C. The addition of a methoxy group (-OCH3) increases the molecular weight and introduces a hydrogen bond acceptor, which can increase the melting point. The presence of a single methoxy group can increase the melting point by approximately 20-30°C.
